# MIR Optimization Module - Mid-level IR optimizations

Mid-level IR optimizations: constant folding, dead code elimination,
common subexpression elimination, loop optimizations, and inlining.

## Optimization Passes

- Constant folding and propagation
- Dead code elimination (DCE)
- Common subexpression elimination (CSE)
- Copy propagation
- Loop optimizations
- Function inlining

## Quick Start

```simple
# Example 1: Run all optimizations
use compiler_core.mir_opt.{optimize_mir}

val optimized = optimize_mir(mir_code, level: 2)
print "Optimized: {optimized.instructions.len()} instructions"
```

```simple
# Example 2: Constant folding
use compiler_core.mir_opt.{constant_fold}

val folded = constant_fold("x = 2 + 3")
# Result: x = 5
```

```simple
# Example 3: Dead code elimination
use compiler_core.mir_opt.{dead_code_elimination}

val cleaned = dead_code_elimination(mir_code)
print "Removed: {original_size - cleaned.size} instructions"
```

```simple
# Example 4: Inline small functions
use compiler_core.mir_opt.{inline_functions}

val inlined = inline_functions(mir_code, threshold: 10)
print "Inlined: {inlined.inlined_count} functions"
```

## Public API

- `use compiler_core.mir_opt.mod.{optimize_mir, OptimizationPass}`
- `use compiler_core.mir_opt.const_fold.{constant_fold}`
- `use compiler_core.mir_opt.dce.{dead_code_elimination}`
- `use compiler_core.mir_opt.inline.{inline_functions}`

